# Sentinel Table Knowledge Base — Reference Sources

## Overview

To build a complete and scalable table knowledge base we use two primary Microsoft sources for all standard tables, and supplement with our own internal reference for third party and custom tables. This document outlines what each source provides, how to use it, and how the knowledge base grows over time.

---

## Source 1 — Microsoft Sentinel Tables & Connectors Reference

**URL:** https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/sentinel/sentinel-tables-connectors-reference

### What It Is
The official Microsoft reference that maps every standard Sentinel table to the data connector responsible for ingesting it.

### What It Gives You
| Field | Available |
|---|---|
| Table Name | Yes |
| Associated Data Connector | Yes |
| DCR Support | Yes |
| Lake-only Ingestion Support | Yes |

### How We Use It
- Primary source for populating the **DataConnector** field in the table watchlist
- Used to identify which tables are associated with which connector during onboarding
- Used to cross-reference connector configuration against expected tables
- Scrapeable — use this to pre-populate the table watchlist for all standard Microsoft tables

### Limitations
- Does not include third party vendor tables ending in `_CL`
- Does not include custom client tables
- Does not provide table descriptions or schema details
- Does not tell you if a table supports multiple data sources

---

## Source 2 — Azure Monitor Log Analytics Table Reference by Category

**URL:** https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/reference/tables-category

### What It Is
The official Microsoft reference for every Log Analytics table organized by category. Each table links to its own individual page with full schema and column definitions.

### What It Gives You
| Field | Available |
|---|---|
| Table Name | Yes |
| Category | Yes — tables are organized by category |
| Description | Yes — on each individual table page |
| Full Schema / Column Definitions | Yes — on each individual table page |
| SingleSource Inference | Yes — derivable from schema columns |

### How We Use It
- Primary source for populating the **Category** and **Description** fields in the table watchlist
- Used to infer **SingleSource** — if a table schema contains columns like `Computer`, `SourceSystem`, `DeviceVendor`, or `HostName` it is designed for multiple sources
- Each table page linked from this index is scrapeable for description and schema details
- Categories from this reference become our standard category taxonomy

### Limitations
- Does not cover third party vendor tables ending in `_CL`
- Does not cover custom client tables
- Does not include connector mapping — use Source 1 for that

