## Source 3 — Internal Third Party Reference (To Be Built)

### What It Is
Our own internal knowledge base for third party and custom tables that are not covered by Microsoft documentation. Built and maintained by the team over time as new client environments are onboarded.

### What It Will Give You
| Field | How It Gets Populated |
|---|---|
| Table Name | Discovered via Usage query in workspace |
| Category | Manually assigned during client review |
| Description | Sourced from vendor documentation or manual inspection |
| Data Connector | From Content Hub or vendor documentation |
| SingleSource | Determined by inspecting actual data in workspace |
| Notes | Added during client review |

### How We Build It
1. When a `_CL` table is discovered in a workspace via the Usage query it gets flagged for review
2. During the client review session the table is investigated — what is writing to it, what vendor, what purpose
3. Details are documented and added to the internal reference
4. Over time this reference grows to cover all common third party tables across our client base
5. Eventually this reference can also be used to pre-populate watchlists for clients using the same third party tools

